args:
Facing off against Qitian Dasheng, Xuan Zang
prepares to take responsibility as a teacher
and end him herself. However, the prince's
dauntless hope persuades her to seek out
and free her possessed student, no matter
how long it may take.
Be wary! I sense the influence\nof the Jin Gu Er nearby!
That's the same kind of fiend that had\nthe Jin Gu Er!
And there are so many of them!\nWhatever is happening here?
They are likely fiends created by\nWu Kong...or rather, by the Jin Gu Er.
AAAA HA HA HA! This is the BEST!\nThe power keeps on coming and coming!
Now rage, my fiends! Unleash your fury!\nRaze and destroy to your hearts' content!
You again? Pah! What do you think\nabout my power NOW, huh?!

There ain't a Qilin relic in the world I
can't seal in two seconds flat now,
which means you MUST recognize
my skills as a sealer!
You speak nonsense. To be ensnared\nby the power of a Qilin relic is the very\nheight of shame for a sealer.
I could never acknowledge you as a\nsealer when you have broken our most\nfundamental of taboos.
Wait, you STILL won't acknowledge me?\nYou are seriously gonna make me lose it!
Well then, maybe if I destroy EVERYTHING,\nthis frustration will be gone too!\nGRAAAAAAAAAAGH!
Urk... A-as both a sealer and your teacher,\nI cannot allow you to go free in this state.
O power universal, hear my decree!\nEternal coffin, shatter all—
Yeaaah, I ain't falling for that again.
...M-master? Why are you on the ground?\nWhat...what did I do?
Did Wu Kong take control again?!
Wu Kong, would you hurry up and ditch\nthat piece-of-crap relic already?!
N-no... I can't... I...don't know\nwhat I'm doing anymore...
Cast off the power of the Jin Gu Er!
I'm sorry I was...such a terrible pupil...
I can't hold it back any longer, master!\nI'm not going to be myself anymore!\nDo it, now!
I will not let your determination\namount to nothing!

O power universal, hear my decree!
Eternal coffin, principle of heaven,
rule of earth! Shatter all boundaries
and reveal infinity itself!
Hah, NOW you're respecting my\n＂determination＂? You've done nothing\nbut hold me back this entire time!
I WILL RETURN! I WILL BE BACK!\nJUST...YOU...WAAAAAIT!
Looks like we got him trapped in the space\nbetween worlds for now at least.
What will you do next, Xuan Zang?
I will of course go there myself and put\na stop to him. Even if it costs me my life.
Hold up. What the heck are you planning\nhere?!
He is my student.\nI will be the one to end him.
When did THIS become the plan?!\nWe got him back to normal once before,\nright? That means we can do it again!
Yet that would only lead to the cycle\nrepeating itself. I have no choice!
I told you of how Qilin relics came from\nthe Qilin people of antiquity, yes?
What I may not have mentioned, however,\nis how those Qilin people came to ruin.
It is said this came about because they\nwere enthralled by the selfsame relics\nthey had themselves created.
Not just themselves—they eventually\ndestroyed the known world itself.
In much the same way, I fear Wu Kong\ncan no longer escape the thrall of\nthe Jin Gu Er.
And if true...then I can at least\nend him myself.
You might be right that Wu Kong will fall\nprey to the Jin Gu Er's power again if we\nrestore him to normal.
And that is why I will—
But if that happens, we'll just do it again.
Twice, three times, it doesn't matter.\nWe'll do it again and again until he can\nfinally break clear of the relic's power.
Now that's what I call a plan!
It's way too early to give up on the kid!
Not repeating the failures of the ancient\nQilin people is indeed an imposing task.
However, there is no guarantee the \nconclusions will always be the same\nas they were before.
Even if we have failed before,\nthe road ahead is unknown.
So believe in the future, Xuan Zang—\nAND the present!
I fear we Qilin have a bad habit of\nworrying overmuch.
I had thought myself better than this,\nand yet when the moment finally arrived...\nWell, it seems I am Qilin after all.
But like you all, I will choose to believe\nin the future from now on!
Then let's go save Wu Kong together!
Give me a little more time, Wu Kong.\nI am coming for you.
